items.abstract:
<jats:p>The paper presents a test stand for measurements of fatigue crack propagation. The stand
includes a fatigue machine MZGS–100 and a device for registration of the crack length. The test
stand is equipped with a stereoscopic microscope with fluent magnification of 7× – 67.5×. The
microscope can be applied for observation of fatigue crack development. The microscope is also
equipped with a digital camera, which enables continuous observation of fatigue crack development
on the computer monitor and it is not necessary to stop the machine. The test results obtained at this
stand can be used for determination of fatigue life and fatigue crack propagation rate.</jats:p>
title: Test Stand for Analysis of Fatigue Crack Propagation under Bending with Torsion
